cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI 

The paper focuses on information-theoretic bounds and approximations in the context of neural population coding, which is a subfield of computational neuroscience. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with information theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely category. The paper involves optimization problems, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses techniques of variable transformation, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
